      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented QA procedures and version-controlled case files meets MRL 2 requirement.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is used under a validated installation with documented regression tests. Case files are version-controlled in a Git repository with change logs. QA level 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark test results from solver vendor and published literature demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations for rotating-frame turbulent flow.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against the Taylor-Couette benchmark and the FDA nozzle benchmark. Published verification studies confirm second-order spatial accuracy for the discretisation schemes employed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for wall shear stress and haemolysis index on a three-mesh refinement study.",
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh refinement study using coarse (4.2 M), medium (9.8 M) and fine (22.1 M) cell counts yielded GCI values of 3.1% for haemolysis index and 4.7% for peak wall shear stress. The medium mesh is selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental flow conditions replicate the five CFD operating points within ±3% on flow rate and rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "Bench tests were conducted at 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6 L/min at 2500 RPM and 3500 RPM. Measured flow rates agreed with CFD boundary conditions within 1.8% and rotational speed within 0.5%, satisfying the acceptance criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) within ±25% of measured NIH across all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "NIH predictions ranged from 8% below to 19% above measured values across the five operating points, with a mean absolute percentage error of 12.4%. The acceptance criterion of ±25% is met at all points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoI (relative haemolysis index RH) directly maps to the clinical acceptance criterion and is computable from CFD outputs without additional transformation assumptions.",
      "rationale": "RH is defined as the ratio of predicted NIH for the candidate pump to that of the predicate device. Both NIH values are computed from the same power-law haemolysis model applied to CFD-derived shear stress histories, ensuring direct relevance to the COU decision criterion."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments use the same pump geometry, blood analogue fluid and operating range as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry with a 36% glycerol-water blood analogue at the same five flow-speed combinations specified in the COU. Geometric and flow similarity is confirmed, satisfying relevance at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 given commercial solver with vendor-supplied verification documentation.",
      "rationale": "Solver round-off and iterative convergence errors are below double-precision machine epsilon for all residuals (< 1e-6). Formal solver error quantification beyond convergence monitoring is not required at MRL 2 and is scoped out."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification and peer review provide adequate control.",
      "rationale": "CFD analyses were performed by a PhD-level analyst with 8 years of cardiovascular CFD experience and independently reviewed by a second qualified analyst. Formal use-error quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form selection is justified by published precedent for centrifugal blood pump CFD.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model combined with the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law haemolysis model is the accepted standard for centrifugal blood pump CFD per FDA guidance and published literature. Formal model-form uncertainty analysis is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key input parameters (haemolysis power-law coefficients, blood viscosity, inlet velocity profile) are specified with documented sources and nominal uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Haemolysis model coefficients (C = 3.62e-5, α = 2.416, β = 0.785) are taken from Giersiepen et al. (1990) with ±15% coefficient of variation reported in the literature. Blood analogue viscosity is measured at 37°C (3.5 mPa·s ± 0.1 mPa·s). Inlet velocity profiles are derived from Doppler ultrasound measurements. Input uncertainty bounds are documented; a full sensitivity analysis characterising which inputs dominate output variance is planned for a follow-on study and is not included in this package."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; single pump specimen used for validation is representative of nominal manufacturing.",
      "rationale": "One pump specimen was used for all bench validation tests. Dimensional inspection confirmed geometry within ±0.05 mm of CAD nominal. Sample-to-sample variability assessment is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; boundary condition equivalency is addressed under Test conditions factor.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the validation experiment and the COU simulation is covered by the Test conditions factor assessment above. A separate formal equivalency analysis is not required at MRL 2."
